Land Rovers are respected and well-loved, and all of them – Range Rover, Discovery and Defenders – now boast maximum safety awards. Thomas Mueller, executive director of product engineering, Jaguar Land Rover, said, “It’s our ambition to design and build the safest vehicles for our clients. Digital innovations and the introduction of new ADAS technologies have allowed us to maintain safety standards at the highest level while preserving the versatility and capability associated with vehicles that wear the Discovery badge.” Advanced driver assistance systems offered on the Land Rover Discovery Sport include lane assist, emergency lane keep assist, 3D surround camera, ClearSight Ground View and adaptive cruise control. Source: MotorPress